The paper deals with dynamic algorithms and data structures for parameterized problems, which suggests that it could belong to categories related to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The specific problems studied in the paper are graph and hitting set problems, which are often studied in computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper also considers lower bounds and hardness hypotheses, which are often studied in theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
